comments.body: ![Screen Shot 2020-02-27 at 2 15 03 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9905193/75478921-bb2f4a00-596c-11ea-8ccb-b678f2c90d2e.png)
@eliotjordan I updated the format.

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/commit/dc9266f5386acafda4788804a559a288cbf2e930 and https://github.com/samvera/browse-everything/commit/61b352736b84a739193e72b5907b589a79c52573 were necessary in order to support single-file uploads using BE in the "File Manager" interface.

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/commit/c7709af29f6463855ffd5699ba9c0b0f5392357f and https://github.com/samvera/browse-everything/commit/173dd8bea04a5f5f9b1ac3659e174495306b61b3 provide support for bulk ingestion (but I am finding some strange behavior with derivative generation - I am not certain if this is just an issue local to my environment, as derivatives were generating without problems for single TIFFs).

https://github.com/samvera/browse-everything/commit/6a4bfd07cadf661e41186024d4481cd6fabf76e1 was needed in order to retrieve more information about the directory tree when ingesting MVWs. There is also now some caching for this in order to increase performance.

https://github.com/samvera/browse-everything/commit/f1790ec137d34b1dd059dcac6dcf2921f687155c and https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/commit/816e499c46e7692a2802ec1a1a74a0d532fb76d5 were needed to resolve some issues with MVW structure during ingests, and in order to fix derivative generation. I will now try and see about testing this more thoroughly with Google Drive.
Passing env. variables by following https://github.com/rails/webpacker/blob/master/docs/env.md is not working as expected - perhaps this is due to the fact that I am importing the JS using an Engine?
https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/commit/2212ef862785d8b6cfbfee332d1f816fec107b40 supports integration for ingesting Archival Media Collection Bags.

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/commit/c91c77e9c4efef166ba51a0ba00fe44e1fd403f2 was needed in order to prevent certain errors from being raised within the Bootstrap Modal component (this was somehow related to a conflict in event handling within Material UI components).
